<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idedf361ce-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s96"><num value="96">§ 96.</num><heading> Punishment for violation of prohibition</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Any person willfully violating any provision of <ref href="/us/usc/t7/s95">section 95 of this title</ref> shall, on conviction, be punished for each offense by a fine not exceeding $5,000 or by imprisonment for not exceeding one year, or both.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idedf361cf-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">(<ref href="/us/act/1923-03-03/ch217/s6">Mar. 3, 1923, ch. 217, § 6</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/42/1436">42 Stat. 1436</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
